#Bitcoin Weekly Forecast📌‼️ Oct. 30 - Nov.05 Key insights for the #crypto market this week? 1/ ~17% weekly pump. A game-changer? 2/ Various scenarios we might encounter. 3/ Shifting stance quickly is a vital part of trading success. ⇢ Recap of last week: In my last Bitcoin Weekly Forecast, I acknowledged that the recent $BTC pump exceeded my expectations. I also emphasized the persistent rise of $BTC dominance, indicating its strength relative to #ETH, #Altcoins, and even #SPX. If BTC maintains its upward momentum and breaches the $31k - $32k resistance zone, we need to monitor the monthly resistance levels at $35k and $38.4k. The price action unfolded impressively, featuring a substantial green weekly candle from $29.9k to $35.2k (considering the wick) and a weekly close at $34.5k.  Though if we have a bearish stance, we can argue that $BTC closed at monthly resistance ($35k), it did surpass previous weekly resistance levels. This ~17% pump, at this stage, appears as a potential game-changer, introducing significant uncertainty into the mix. ⇢ Facing multiple scenarios ahead: We will have a new $BTC monthly candle in 2 days, and this monthly close matters a lot. 1⃣If the monthly close is above $35k, it's super bullish, with targets set at $37.2k - $38.4k and the possibility of surging past $40k. 2⃣Monthly close between $32k - $35k is bullish as well, especially following a positive weekly close above $32k. Avoiding a sharp drop in the next 2 days maintains the bullish outlook, and we aim for the same targets as in Scenario 1 after a minor pullback. 3⃣Monthly close below $32k is bearish, signaling a probable return to the previous range at $26k - $28k. So in summary, the market may either pump with or without a shallow pullback, leaving the sideliner away, or experience a sharp drop, confirming the recent pump as a trap for traders. Either a upcoming pump or dump will be a big one. People who expect a decent pull back to ~30k to get in the car may not get a chance to do so. ⇢ Shifting stance quickly is a vital part of trading success🚩. To be honest, I'm currently taking a neutral stance, without a bias toward either bullish or bearish. My trading setups will align with how $BTC's price evolves. It's crucial to highlight the importance of taking profits. Three months ago, I sold my spot $BTC and shorted at $31.2k, closing out at $25.8k. I later repurchased spot and went long, closing my long positions at $28k, but I'm still holding onto those spots. You can track all these trades on my timeline. Timely profit-taking grants me flexibility when price action deviates slightly from expectations, allowing for new trading setups. In trading, perfection isn't attainable. What truly matters is how we adapt to different price movements. ⇢ If you enjoyed my forecasts and analysis, please don’t forget to: ☆ Follow me for market insights on #BTC, #crypto and #stocks. ☆ Like, RT, bookmark and drop a comment.

📈Brazil's #USDT adoption is soaring in 2023, comprising a whopping 80% of all crypto transactions. 💹🚀 

"USDT has seen a significant surge in adoption in Brazil, accounting for 80% of all #cryptocurrency  transactions in the country so far in 2023.

As of mid-October, #USDT transactions in Brazil this year amounted to $271 billion Brazilian reais (~$55 billion), almost double the volume of Bitcoin

USDT transactions have been on the rise in Brazil since 2021, but crossed Bitcoin volume for the first time in July 2022, just at the peak of the crypto industry’s storm last year, when crypto lenders Three Arrows Capital and Voyager Capital collapsed.

The crypto winter slashed the volume of crypto transactions in the country by nearly 25% in 2022, ending at $154.4 billion reais, or ~$31 billion, the government reported.

The Brazilian tax agency tracks crypto-related activities of citizens using a sophisticated system that relies on artificial intelligence and network analysis. According to a blog post, the system is able to detect suspicious activity as well as trace the location of individuals trading cryptocurrencies.

The revenue agency is also targeting crypto investments held by the country’s citizens overseas. On Oct. 25, the local Congress passed legislation that recognizes cryptocurrencies as “financial assets” for tax purposes in foreign investments. Earnings overseas between 6,000 and 50,000 reais (~$10,000) will be subject to a 15% tax rate starting in January 2024. Above this threshold, taxes will be applied at 22.5%.

Since 2019, crypto exchanges operating in Brazil are required to disclose all user transactions to the government. Capital gains from crypto sales exceeding 35,000 reais (~7,000) per month are subject to a progressive tax bracket of 15% to 22.50%.

Global crypto exchanges such as Coinbase, Binance, Bitso, and http://Crypto.com operate in the country alongside local players such as Mercado Bitcoin and Foxbit."
